column14: Advice

column13: Kill 8 deck-hands, 10 look-outs, 3 brutes, then boss
column14:
The path through the Corsair camp is mostly West and South, and slightly up the hill.
There are stealthed Corsair Cutthroats along the path.
Group mobs and AoE them down. 
Ghasaphâr spawns at [20.2S, 110.2W]
The scout will appear at roughly the same location.

column13: Heal X crewmates, kill X corsairs
column14: Group mobs and AoE down.
Run to the end, AoE mobs, collect boxes on way back to starting point, kill boss.
Ignore mobs, go straight to boss. Find nearby scout and leave immediately once boss is dead.

column13: Kill crabs, click nets, kill boss
column14: Group mobs and AoE down.

column13: Collect 10 research papers,destroy 8 gredbyg nests, kill boss
column14: Ignore initial rockworms. Group gredbyg and click things. You can outrun many gredbyg to get clickables faster. Some gredbyg don't aggro.

column13: Kill 12 corsairs, collect treasure, kill boss
column14: Group mobs and AoE down. There are more mobs than needed. Ignore mobs on lowest beach. Head south. Boss counts as one of the 12. Three spirits spawn when you approach treasure.

column13: Kill 16 undead corsairs, free 4 captives, kill boss
column14: Group mobs and AoE down. Boss is near ship where you free woman. Head south-west, towards prow of ship.

column13: Kill 18 crabs, repair 10 leaks, then kill 2 great crabs
column14: Group mobs and AoE down.
column15: Buggy floors. Mobs may drop through. You may bounce around a bit.
column16: Bugs make this one to avoid.

column14: Non-combat. Ignore gredbyg. Use delete key to find next clickables.

column13: Kill 8 huorns and 6 wildwoods, then boss
column14: Group mobs and AoE down. It can be easy to miss a mob at start and have to backtrack. Boss spawns at back. Scout spawns closer to entrance.
column16: The most tedious new mission, too similar to daily.

column14: Run straight, then left, up to top of hill and kill Svalfang and adds.
Must collect 10 bombs and 10 crates (While not required, you're forced to kill almost everything in the dungeon to do this.)
Aggressive Skirmish-like mission, where you can pull lots of mobs and AoE. Must reclaim several locations.

Kill 15 mobs, burn 8 banners. Best to run through to pick up all mobs and AoE down, then burn banners after. Once done, face a wave of mobs at entrance and down below. Then return to summong horn to end.
Kill mobs and collect crates and keys to unlock doors.
Timed defensive mission, where you have to wait between waves. No way to speed this up.
Two locations, kill mobs and collect things, then return to middle.
Kill all orcs in courtyard. 3 pulls of 3 mobs, plus pathers. Difficulty depends on pull.
Can pull multiple sets, lots of mobs. Kill gauntmen first.
Reach camp at top (camp is immediately right at top of stairs). Several pulls of ~5 mobs. Orcs sometimes drop down. Kill Ork Gates on way. Defilers can heal gates.
Kill mobs and gates and get across bridge. You only need to reach the end of bridge, not kill mobs.
Single mob pulls, can avoid centre mobs, cocoons can spawn dwarves or orcs.

Kill 8 Jorthkyn AND their hounds (scout won't appear until then). They come with hounds. 2 mobs per pull. After final Jorthkyn, scout spawns on top and you can leave. Can avoid some hounds/summons if you focus Jorthkyn.
Kill mobs, click banners. More mobs than needed.
Destroy catapults and towers. Can avoid some mobs. 1-2 mobs per pull. Pathers. Can be hard to move around, so can pull extra.
Pathers come towards you at start (possible to pull a set and then have pathers). Mostly pulls of 2 mobs, one of 3. Kill all mobs.
Must approach cats with rings on to patrol locations, spawns mobs, also pathers, can get swarmed with mobs. Must kill all for scout to spawn.
Kill wargs and 3 boss. 3 per pull. More wargs than necessary. Bosses don't count as wargs.
Mostly solo pulls, boss and 2 mobs at end.
12 mobs, 3 plans. Must kill all mobs. Easy enough on t10. Can pull 1-2 mobs at time.
Kill orcs and boss. Boss is either in ruins on left or ruins down on right (it's random). More mobs than necessary. Can get bad first pull if not careful.
Find and kill boss (Dargund). He can be in multiple locations (up and down to right). Scout spawns where mob does. Tracking helps.

Looks like you can get single pulls, but there are pathers and stealthed mobs, can end up with very large pulls. At end, boss paths, then runs to house and summons 3 waves of 3 adds before he engages (seemed almost broken). Can be cheated if you can one-shot boss.

column3: Mission: The Ruins of Amon Firn
column14: Need to kill half-orc captain only. He's on far east, down from mountain (can be upstairs or downstairs, possibly other locations). Can avoid many mobs if careful. Lots of mobs around. Difficulty and length depend on how succesful you are at avoiding mobs.

Kill mobs and boss. Boss can spawn in multiple locations (centre, south ruins). Boss greenbars twice, resets twice, and summons extra waves of adds. Potentially more difficult on other variants, as uruks don't summon on death in Variant B (bug?).
Harder pulls, 4+ mobs. Pulling 1 sometimes makes 3 more appear. Tight spaces, so hard to move. 2-3 pulls, then talk to questgiver.
Kill all mobs, including summoned mobs and boss, then click brazier. Brazier can't be clicked while in combat.
Kill 15 mobs. More mobs than necessary. 4 upstairs. 1-4 mobs per pull. Some pathing.
~5-6 pulls, 3-4 mobs, pathers. Hard to see puddles on ground. Hard to move around. Boss spawns 3 mobs.
Kill 15 wood trolls. No extra mobs. 1-2 per pull, but can pull additional. Scout in centre.
Kill 16 wolf-keepers, but they come with a wolf each, so it's 32 mobs. Very easy to get multiple pulls. Pathing mobs.
Kill 15 brigands, 2 lieutenants and boss.
Help/burn victims (only click them once or it will bug). You have to fight wargs to get to many, but 2-3 per pull.
Can pull multiple sets easily, pathers, can get a lot of mobs.
Must survive for ~7 mins, then find scout. Scout doesn't spawn until a certain number of mobs are killed. Insane number of mobs will aggro.
Reach top of stairs and kill boss. Be careful when you go up initial stairs, mobs aggro on either side, so can pull too much.
Defeat Blogmal gang-leader. He's at bottom (stairs on right). Can avoid most mobs on Variant A, but need 3-4 pulls on Variant B.

column3: Mission: The Tombs of Gond Orchal
column14: All solo pulls, very spread apart, easy to do as a result.
Lots of pathers, can get bad pulls if not careful. Can pull some single pathers.
2 mobs per pull, mobs don't spawn new mobs on kill. Puddle does small damage.
Kill mobs, collect things. More mobs than necessary. Usually 1 mob per pull. Uruks (no summons on death on Variant B)
Find and kill commander (he's upstairs in back on right). He's not the captain. Pulling commander pulls nearby group. Can just kill him and leave.
Must kill everything in courtyard, including captain, before scout appears.

column3: Mission: A Day on the Farm
column14: First part is easy, single mob pulls. When you click final burrow, crebain spawn, so you get 3 crebain + 1 shrew. Must kill 3 more sets of 3 crebain.
Burn towers, must kill mobs around them.
Deliver 2 pies (quest/pie is a lie), kill 4-5 pulls of brigands, 15 total, 3-4 per pull. Can be hard to move around on platforms.
Kill 15 wolves and 1 boss. Can get a bad pull of two waves. Waves are 2-3 mobs. Must kill all mobs.
